<TITLE> BOA tackles food management </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 12 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Olympic Association has asked all the federations related to the upcoming SA Games to include two players with the food management of the training camp in a bid to improve the quality of food. The BOA, in a letter on Thursday, requested the federations to form respective mess committee involving two of the players. The mess committee would oversee the catering process. It has been learnt that BOA took the decision following its president General Moeen U Ahmed's direction. A BOA source said that the president expressed dissatisfaction at some news items in print and electronic media over players' complaints over quality of food in the camp. The source said the players' involvement with the catering process would not create any added pressure to their training. On the other hand, it would put the food supplier under pressure. The BOA has been providing Taka 300 for each player of the ongoing camps. bd
